<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html lang="en" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head>
<meta charset="utf-8" />
<title>word-break: break-all, spacing vowel sign</title>
<meta content="word-break: break-all means lines may break between any two typographic letter units. A spacing vowel sign should be wrapped to the next line with its base character." name="assert" />
<link href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css-text-3/#word-break-property" rel="help" />
<link href="reference/word-break-break-all-ref-006.xht" rel="match" />
<link href="mailto:ishida@w3.org" rel="author" title="Richard Ishida" />
<style type="text/css">
.test { word-break: break-all; }
/* the CSS below is not part of the test */
.test, .ref { border: 1px solid orange;  margin: 20px;  padding: 10px; width: 390px; font: 36px/1.5 sans-serif; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div id="instructions">Test passes if the two orange boxes are the same.</div>
<div lang="hi" class="test"><div id="testdiv"><span id="testspan">हिंदी हिंदी हिंदी</span></div></div>
<div lang="hi" class="ref"><span>हिंदी हिंदी हिं<br />दी</span></div>
<script>
var sentenceWidth = document.getElementById('testspan').offsetWidth
document.getElementById('testdiv').style.width = String(sentenceWidth - 5)+'px'
</script>
<!--
Notes:
A typographic unit based on extended grapheme clusters groups base characters and combining characters together.
-->

</body></html>